  "body": "In IBFT 2.0 genesis file, there is `miningbeneficiary` field. \r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"config\": {\r\n    \"ibft2\": {\r\n      \"miningbeneficiary\": \"0xfe3b557e8fb62b89f4916b721be55ceb828dbd73\"\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf this field is omitted, then a block reward goes to a validator that proposes the block.\r\nIf this field is set, then there is only one single `miningbeneficiary` who always receives the full block reward.\r\n\r\nMy question is: Is it possible to configure mining reward to be split between validator that proposes the block and the one single `miningbeneficiary`. Let's say the reward is split 80:20?",
